This new research, carried out in a Scottish Highlands county, is trying to find out how bats use the landscape in their search for food.
Everything that is learned will shed more light on the behaviour of the only flying mammals and help guide future conservation efforts.
The study, carried out by the National Trust for Scotland, will follow common and soprano pipistrelle bats, as well as Daubenton's bat and brown long-eared bat from Inverewe Gardens in Wester Ross.
