American golfer Phil Mickelson, who had to fight hard for most of the tournament, admitted defeat by hitting his tee shot into the water on the par-3 16th hole, conceding defeat to Francesco Molinari.
Italian golfer Francesco Molinari excelled in all his rounds, becoming one of four players to ever shoot a 5-0-0 since the current format of the tournament began in 1979.
American Jordan Spieth lost to the lowest-ranked player on the European team, Denmark's Thorbjorn Olesen, 5 and 4.
World number one Dustin Johnson fell 2 and 1 to Englishman Ian Poulter, who might have played his last Ryder Cup.
Sergio García, a veteran who has won eight Ryder Cups, became the European with the most victories in the history of the tournament, with 25.5 points in his career.
