Woods lost all four matches in France and now has a 13-21-3 record in his Ryder Cup career.
This is an unusual statistic for one of the greatest players of all time, who has won 14 major titles, trailing only Jack Nicklaus.
The American team had to fight all weekend to find the streets, with the exception of Patrick Reed, Justin Thomas and Tony Finau, who played great golf all weekend.
